cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a new algorithm for cloud and cloud shadow detection in optical satellite remote sensing imagery using deep convolutional neural network. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The algorithm utilizes ResNet, a deep residual network, for pixel-level cloud mask generation. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an AI-based solution for cloud and cloud shadow detection in satellite remote sensing images. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper deals with processing and analysis of satellite remote sensing images, which falls under the domain of computer graphics. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes an algorithm for automated detection of cloud and cloud shadow in satellite remote sensing images, which can be useful in robotics applications such as autonomous navigation.
